args: *pant* *wheeze* According to the info\nI got my hands on, the Su Jindan is\nsomewhere in this mountain range...
Too bad this place is FREAKIN' HUGE!\nWhere the heck IS this stupid relic?!
*sigh* Did you truly believe you would\nrandomly stumble upon a fated hidden\nrelic if you simply nosed about?
No one invited you, Yulong! ...Uh oh.\nDid my master tell you to come\nhere and bring me back?
The opposite, in fact: Xuan Zang ordered\nme to assist you in your search.
She is presently occupied performing a\nduty in Master Fa Ming's place, and so\ncannot lend aid in the matter herself.
Thus, she sent me to keep watch.\nShe is...terribly worried about you.
Oh man. If I'm making her sweat, I've\nREALLY gotta hurry up and find this thing.\nAnyway, thanks for the help.
Indeed, I hope my ability to sense the\npresence of Qilin relics will prove useful.
Hey, so while we're looking, how about\nyou let me ride on your back? I've been\nhoofin' it for days now, and I'm beat.

Xuan Zang's command was to ascertain
the Su Jindan's whereabouts—she said
nothing about allowing foolish boys to
ride me like a common mule.
Yeah, but SHE always gets to\nride around on your back!
But of course! It is my supreme pleasure\nand delight to bear Xuan Zang across\nthe skies!
Uh, you say some weird stuff sometimes.\nYou know that, right?
*sigh* We've been going around these\nmountains for three days, and still no\nsign of the relic.
It is strange. I have patrolled from the\npeaks of the mountains to the deepest\nvalley depths, and yet sense nothing.
Say, what about that mountain waaaay\nover there? You haven't looked at that\none yet, have you?
*sigh* Why do I feel like you became\na sealer without knowing one whit of\nyour chosen profession's history?
That is a cursed mountain of impurities,\na site that has been taboo since the era\nof the ancient Qilin.
No sealer would dare set foot there.
Which means no one has ever checked\nit out before, right?! Riiiiiight?
Wu Kong, you cannot mean to...\nNo, boy! Wait!
Do you truly mean to enter this place?
Yep! I mean, yeah, I'm sure I'll get a\nlecture about it or whatever, but if the\nSu Jindan could be here, I have to look.
Take care, Wu Kong! This mist...\n...people's...dangerous...
Did you say something, Yulong?\n...Huh? Yulong?
He's gone! Did he go back because he\ndidn't want to get scolded? Sheesh,\ntalk about your obedient little lapdogs...
Welp, nothing to do about it now.\nLooks like I'm searching on my own.
(Just wait, old man—I WILL save you!)
*cough* The mist's getting thicker...\nI can't see two feet in front of me...\nAnd I'm getting...kinda tired...
Huh...? Did I pass out? Where am I?
You did—and only by the luckiest thread\ndo you still cling to the mortal coil.
But hey, what are you even DOING here?\nI thought Qilin all avoided this place.
I've no choice but to hide myself away\nin a place none will ever dare enter.
Enough. I know not your circumstances,\nbut you must make from this place\nwith all haste.
Else you will be swallowed by the mist\nreleased by the Su Jindan.
Wait, THAT jewel is the Su Jindan?!
...Mmm. So in order to save the life of a\ngreat sealer, you need this relic?

Yeah, so I don't know all the details,
but apparently great sealers have been
risking their lives for hundreds of years
to keep the Ling Xuan Dan in check.
But it'd all be fine if we had the Su Jindan,\nso maybe I can just...borrow it?

I would be happy to lend it to you.
And based on what you have told me,
it seems this method might also serve
to nullify the power of THIS relic as well.
Wait, huh? I'm not sure I follow.
It's likely that the Ling Xuan Dan's yin chi\nand the Su Jindan's yang chi will mutually\nnullify each other.
So if the two were to be brought together,\nthere is a high possibility of BOTH\nloathsome mists being eradicated.
You're talking about this mist that's around\nus right now, right?

Yes, and it is a most bothersome thing.
Spending an extended period in its
presence will cause one's essence
to be absorbed into the Su Jindan.
Its victims live on as part of the mist,\ncursed with a sort of sham immortality.
Well, THAT sounds freaky! How'd you\nend up in charge of this little beauty?
When I was a journeying sealer,\nI found the relic about to run wild\nnear a human village.
I could not let this happen, and so took up\nthe relic at once, and ended up trapped\nwithin its terrible thrall.
Once this happened, I knew I had to find\na place where I could exist in solitude\nso as not to threaten the lives of others.
How long has it been? A century? More?\nTime no longer has meaning for me.
All I know is that my very existence\nis now tied to the Su Jindan.
So you've been alone here for all that\ntime just to keep this thing contained?
Like you, I am a sealer; duty demanded\nthat I do what was necessary.
But now, having heard of the existence of\nthis Ling Xuan Dan, that burden has been\nremoved from my mind.
I will entrust my relic to you;\nI have faith you will do what is right.
Of course not! I'll fulfill my sealer duty.

But listen. I'm a human, right? So I
don't really ＂get＂ this resolve you
Qilin have to take responsibility
for your ancestors' actions.
Though you may not grasp it fully,\nyou have taken it on nonetheless.
Yes. Whatever may happen, you will save\nthe sealer called Fa Ming. That is the\nresolve that guides you to act now.
I know this because you have not fled this\nplace even knowing the fearsome power\nthat resides here.
Okay, yeah. I think I understand now—\nand you can absolutely count on me!
Be swift, Wu Kong. Bring the Su Jindan to\nits opposite before the mist fells you.
As I said, my handling of the relic did no\nmore than grant me a false survival.
Without its power, dissolution awaits me.\nOr perhaps I should say...release.
Please, human sealer. Do this for me.
THERE you are, you fool child!
Th-that relic! Wu Kong, it is...?
Yeah, I found it. Er, or I was\nentrusted with it, I guess.
I'll explain on the way. Let's go!
